org.swisscheese.swisscheese

Class Criteria

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.swisscheese.swisscheese.Criteria

  • public class Criteria
extends java.lang.Object

    Where is the criteria of the project met?

    Inheritance

    By criteria this project must contain an inheritance hierarchy of an abstract class and sub-classes of the abstract class.

    Abstract class:

    The abstract class that was made for this project is Renderer, which is used to render the frame onto the screen.

    Abstract class method criteria:

    The criteria is met in the following classes. There may be more methods that fit the criteria.
    • Abstract method: Renderer.isMultithreaded()
    • Regular method (overridden): Renderer.render(int[])
    • Final methods:
      1. Renderer#fillBackground()
      2. Renderer.getMover()
    • Static Method: Renderer.changeTextures(org.swisscheese.swisscheese.texturePacks.TexturePack)

    Classes extending Renderer:

    • SingleThreadedRenderer
    • MultithreadedRendererDispatcher
      • StripRendererDispatcher
      • ChunkRendererDispatcher

    Sub-class criteria

    • Exclusive methods:
      • SingleThreadedRenderer:SingleThreadedRenderer.getAverageRenderingTime() -> returns average time for rendering of 10 passes
      • MultithreadedRendererDispatcher: MultithreadedRendererDispatcher.getMultiDetails() -> converts RendererDetails of Renderer to MultithreadedRendererDetails to include number of threads used.

    Polymorphism:

    The only way to create an Renderer object is to use RendererFactory

    Collections of Objects

    List of some collections used in the game:
    • Deque (as a stack): Generator log of CellGrid.Direction enums
    • Deque (as a queue): StripRendererDispatcher and ChunkRendererDispatcher to collect a queue of multi-threading Future
    • Map: Keyboard: stores Keys enums as values and virtual keyboard codes (Integer) as keys.
    • List: TexturePackList stores TexturePack objects

    About this class:
    This class provides javadoc and information on the criteria met in the project. Does not have any uses besides javadoc.
    For more info about installing this game, see read me file on Gitlab.
